cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI

The paper discusses a steganographic method that utilizes multimedia communication protocols like RTP. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, since the paper focuses on the practical evaluation of the LACK method, cs.CR and cs.MM are the most likely categories. The other categories are less likely as they are not directly related to the method's implementation and evaluation.
